title: Cross section and angular anisotropy of fission of U-238,Bi-209,Pb-208-206 and Au-197 by 70-200 MeV protons.

x4freetext: Cross section and angular anisotropy of fission of
protons.
In Russian

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Soviet Journal of Nuclear Physics, Vol.17, p.496 (1973)

x4freetext: In English
The target thickness was determined in the case of
uranium by counting the alpha particles, with accuracy
1%, and in other cases by weighing, with accuracy 2%.
The target diameter was 20 mm, and the proton beam
diameter was 10 mm.
The protons were monitored with an induction pickup
calibrated against the induced activity in the reaction
C-12(p,pn)C-ll
The solid track detectors (GLASS).
